pr_title: Created Contract Class with Draft, Deploy and Mint Methods
pr_body:
Fixes #7 , Fixes #8 , Fixes #10

## Changes
- Created Contract Class. Initialization for both new and existing contracts possible. Used [Ethers.js](https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js) for connecting to blockchains.
- Implemented the Draft method for generating a Solidity Smart Contract with the help of [Open Zeppelin Wizard](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/contracts-wizard)
- Implemented Deploy Method for deploying Smart Contract to a Blockchain network
- Implemented Mint Method for interacting with deployed Smart Contract and minting a new NFT.
- Added Examples for Draft, Deploy and Mint functionalities
- Added Test for Draft Method

## Impact
- Draft Functionality for NFT Contracts implemented
- Deploy Functionality for NFT Contracts implemented
- Mint Functionality for NFTs implemented

pr_body:
# Changes
## Added Final changes in **Collection Class** ( created in #14 ).
This class implements the Generate functionality for generating NFT Image and Metadata files from Layer images.
## Created **FileStorage Abstract Class** and the following classes implementing it.
These classes have functions for uploading NFT Collections and Single NFTs to a File Storage platform.
- **NFT.storage Class** for uploading to [NFT.storage](https://nft.storage/)
- **Pinata Class** for uploading to [Pinata](https://www.pinata.cloud/)
- **Storj Class** for uploading to [Storj](https://landing.storj.io/permanently-pin-with-storj-dcs)
- **Infura Class** for uploading to [Infura](https://infura.io/product/ipfs)
- **Arweave Class** for uploading to [Arweave](https://www.arweave.org/) using [Bundlr](https://bundlr.network/)
## Created **Contract Class**.
This class implements the following functionalities.
- Programatically generating (_"Drafting"_) ERC721 and ERC1155 Smart contracts as solidity files.
- Deploying Smart contracts to any of the following Blockchain networks
    - [Ethereum](https://ethereum.org/): Mainnet, Ropsten, Rinkeby, Goerli, Kovan
    - [Polygon](https://polygon.technology/): Mainnet, Mumbai
- Interacting with deployed Smart contracts on any of the above networks
## Added Tests for all the above classes (Collection, NFT.storage, Pinata, Storj, Infura, Arweave, Contract)
## Added Example scripts for each functionality (Generate, Upload, Draft, Deploy and Interact)
## Created Documentation for the project
